ğŸ“¢MISD Update:
Menard ISD has released our official â€œBack to School Surveyâ€ on the school website at www.menardisd.net. We need it completed by August 5th so we can get the data together for both sets of students. Please make sure you understand that home based learning or in class instruction is your choice as a parent or guardian. Each six weeks you can reevaluate your choice prior to the new six weeks starting.
The virtual home learning will be different than last yearâ€™s packets. The Texas Education Agency has put rules and guidance in place for us to create a plan. Your child will have to check in, watch teaching, participate in lessons, and turn in work daily for each subject. If your child does not engage daily, then they will be counted absent for that day. They will be graded on the work that they are doing, and it will not be pass/fail. High school course credit is determined by daily attendance in each class.
Menard ISD at this time will only allow participation in extracurricular if your child is attending in class instruction.

ğŸMenard ISD update:
As per the Executive Order issued by the Governor Abbott of Texas, Menard ISD will be closed but providing home based learning through May 1st. We will provide meals during this closure on Mondays and Thursdays from 11:30-12:30 at the elementary & junior high. We will have packet drop off and pick up April 7th, April 14th, April 21st, and April 28th at your childâ€™s campus from 11:30-12:30. It is imperative that your child is completing these packets. The home based learning documents will be used to determine mastery of grade level and/or course credit. Please contact the teachers by Remind or email if your child needs help. The teachers have also set up other forms of communication to help. The teachers are here to help you during the week.

Thanks to all of you for the continued effort for our school, students, and community. We will all need to work together and with our neighbors.

The home based learning documents will be used to determine mastery of grade level and/or course credit. Please contact the teachers by Remind or email if your child needs help. The teachers have also set up other forms of communication to help. The teachers are here to help you during the week.

Thanks to all of you for the continued effort for our school, students, and community. We will all need to work together and with our neighbors.

ğŸMenard ISD is committed to Supporting students instructionally while at home. This will come in a variety of ways depending on the grade level and the course. We are doing this in an attempt to file for waivers so that students do not have to attend school during the summer.
On Tuesday, March 17, 2020, Teachers will have learning packets ready for you to pick up for your child/children. These packets will be a review of skills that have been taught up to this point in the year. Please come by the school between 11:30-12:30 to pick up your child/childrenâ€™s packet. Someone will be waiting curbside to hand them out. NO lunches provided Tuesday.
WEDNESDAY, March 18, 2020, Menard ISD will be providing lunches for students. Please come to pick up your child/childrenâ€™s lunch between 11:30â€”12:30. The menu is as follows:
Wednesday-Ham and cheese sandwich
Thursday-Corndogs
Friday-Hamburgers
Chips, fruit or veggies, and milk will be provided on each of these days as well.

Menard ISD appreciates the families of Menard helping us keep our community safe! Thank you for your continued support.

post_text:
ğŸ“¢Update from UIL:

To support the health and safety of our students and communities, UIL is suspending all UIL sanctioned contests due to the outbreak of COVID-19 (Coronavirus) in Texas. Effective March 16th, all UIL interscholastic competition is suspended until March 29th. At this time, competitions may resume on March 30th. We are in contact with state authorities and will continue to monitor this situation. Should further adjustments be necessary, we will communicate them to you as soon as they are available.

During this time competitions are suspended, practices and rehearsals may be held at the discretion of the local school district.

Menard ISD will not be attending golf tournaments, softball games, tennis tournaments, UIL academics, or track meets for the next two weeks.
